- User request: 이 게임의 타이틀 화면 구상안을 그래픽디자이너, 기획자, 개발자 다같이 논의시켜
- Executor decision: Use Agent Room routing before subagents. Primary methodology is Superpowers brainstorming. No implementation yet.

## Method Route

- Primary methodology: Superpowers brainstorming
- Supporting methodology: Project policy, Graphic Designer policy, g-stack/browser validation later if implementation starts
- Project policy checked: yes
- Required verification: none for concept-only discussion; browser/mobile validation required before claiming implemented title changes

## Agent Records

### graphic_designer

- Persona: game art and visual direction specialist
- Role: propose title scene visual composition and toon-rendered mood
- Main viewpoint: readability, 3D toon policy, title-scene silhouette, mobile visual hierarchy
- Read/write authority: discussion only; wrote visual direction record
- Output folder: `Graphic_designer/UI_HUD_Title/`
- Output: `title_screen_visual_direction_proposal_2026-05-23.md`

### product-manager

- Persona: product and planning framer
- Role: define what the first screen must communicate and what the MVP should exclude
- Main viewpoint: first 3 seconds, first-run conversion, MVP menu simplicity
- Read/write authority: discussion only
- Output folder: `Planner/Essential_game_plan/`
- Output: incorporated into `title_screen_multi_agent_concept_review_2026-05-23.md`

### game-developer

- Persona: R3F/game implementation specialist
- Role: evaluate current title structure, safe MVP additions, mobile risks, verification gates
- Main viewpoint: current architecture preservation, mobile performance, screen transition safety
- Read/write authority: discussion only
- Output folder: `Developer/`
- Output: `title_screen_technical_discussion_2026-05-23.md`

## Integrated Decision

The title screen should be a fast first-run entry screen, not a heavy landing page.

Recommended direction:

- Keep `Escape! zombie school` as the dominant first read.
- Use one clear subtitle: `감염된 학교에서 5분만 버티면, 교문이 열린다`.
- Keep the primary action as `게임 시작`.
- Do not expose the coin shop on the title screen for MVP.
- Show a 3D toon student survivor facing an exit glow while infection students approach from behind.
- Keep title scene non-interactive and lightweight.

## Do-Not-Skip Rules

- Do not skip `project_develop_policy.md`.
- Do not let subagents replace Superpowers brainstorming.
- Do not put coin shop back on the title screen for MVP without a new product decision.
- Do not implement graphics that violate 3D toon + outline policy.
- Do not call implementation complete without browser/mobile validation.

